{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Inspired by spatial transformer networks [15], PointNet enables learning translationinvariant geometric features by employing a series of shared multilayer perceptrons (MLPs) across vertices or faces, along with a symmetric function such as global max-pooling.",
    "This approach demonstrated promising results by using the raw surface modeled as a point cloud as input.",
    "However, it disregarded the local spatial relationships of 3D shapes, as the network learned features independently for each face.",
    "In recent years, various publications have been published aiming to overcome the limitations of PointNet.",
    "One prominent example is PointNet++ [16], which introduced a hierarchical network structure that groups points into increasingly larger sets and applies PointNets to learn group-wise geometric features."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Inspired by spatial transformer networks [15], PointNet enables learning translationinvariant geometric features by employing a series of shared multilayer perceptrons (MLPs) across vertices or faces, along with a symmetric function such as global max-pooling.",
